</a> and struggled with it. However, many reviewers of that book mentioned the superb quality of this one. They were right. Our book begins with two women walking through a cemetery and discussing the men buried there. Who are these women? What is so significant about this cemetery? Robert Hicks unveils the story of a Southern woman long forgotten in American history who desired to remember the men that had taken part in a bloody civil war and lost their lives because of it.</span>
